    <text>
        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(center)"><placeName>Montgomery</placeName> <date>23 August 1852</date></p>
			<p><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee>.</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">Sir&#33;</p>
			<p>I enclosed send you three Dollars for a copy<lb/> of the Occident&#44; which you have send to the <persName>Rev E.<lb/> Marmson</persName> of this city &#40;formerly.&#41;</p>
			<p>I believe you have been already informed&#44; the<lb/> circumstances&#44; <sic>conected</sic> <sic>whit</sic> the <persName>Rev. E. Marmson</persName><lb/> but if not&#63; I will tell you</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">The Kahl of this city&#8212;&#40;I am not a member&#41;<lb/> had engaged <persName>Mr Marmson</persName> for a year payable<lb/> quarterly at the rate of &#36;500 a year. <sic>Thee</sic> <sic>wuld</sic><lb/> not agree&#44; and <persName>Mr Marmson</persName> send his resignation<lb/> and left them and went to the Ministers of the<lb/> Christian Faith&#44; he has then for the last 6 or 8<lb/> weeks boarded and lodged <sic>whit</sic> them and the<lb/> rumor here in this city&#44; was&#44; that he has been<lb/> converted to the Christian faith&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I meet then <persName>Mr Marmson</persName> and ask him of<lb/> the truth&#44; he then <sic>denided</sic> and said all is<lb/> a Lie&#44; and false. I told him that he should<lb/> to <sic>satisfied</sic> the Brothers of our faith&#44; and the<lb/> <sic>comunity</sic> in <sic>generally</sic>&#44; publish the truth in the city<lb/> papers&#44; under his own signature&#44; which he<lb/> promise me to do it&#44; but in vain he left<lb/> here I do not <sic>wer</sic> he went to and <sic>dit</sic> not <sic>don</sic><lb/> it. I send you this information to satisfy</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>you and our Brothers in the <placeName>United <sic>Stated</sic></placeName> to have<lb/> a look out and to be on their guard.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">And I no say If <persName>Mr Marmson</persName> <sic>dos</sic> not<lb/> publish the truth in your <sic>Pamplet</sic> our Asmonean<lb/> under his own signature&#63;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I will then publish his name over<lb/> the world</p>
          <p rend="indent(6)">More anon</p>
          <p rend="indent(7)">Yours Truly</p>
          <p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">S. Cellner</persName></p>
			<p>P. S.&#160;&#160;The three Dollars for the Occident<lb/>&#160;&#160; I have received of the President<lb/>&#160;&#160; from Kahl for him&#8212;&#8212;</p>
          
        </body>
